# Entity Descriptions

### Division
Represents a department within Regent College London that manages training programmes and workshops. Each division has a name, contact information, and a head of division.

### Programme
Represents a professional training programme offered by the college. A programme belongs to one division and may be accredited by a professional body.

### Workshop
Represents a short course or workshop delivered by the college. Workshops may run as scheduled sessions at different campuses.

### Accrediting Body
Represents an external organisation that accredits programmes or workshops. Examples include BCS, ACCA, and PMI.

### Session
Represents a scheduled instance of a programme or workshop. A session includes date, time, location, campus, and instructor information.

### Campus
Represents one of the Regent College campuses where sessions are delivered. Each campus has an address and capacity details.

### Instructor
Represents a trainer or lecturer responsible for delivering sessions. Instructors have qualifications and a home campus.

### Participant
Represents a person who registers for training sessions or workshops. Participant records include contact details and enrolment information.

### Enrolment
Represents the relationship between participants and sessions. It stores which participant is registered for which session.

