# Starter Glossary

| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| Entity | A real-world object or concept stored in the database, such as Programme or Instructor. |
| Attribute | A property that describes an entity, such as ProgrammeTitle or InstructorName. |
| Relationship | An association between entities, such as a Participant enrolling in a Session. |
| Primary Key | A unique identifier used to distinguish each record in a table. |
| Foreign Key | An attribute that creates a link between two related tables. |
| Constraint | A rule that ensures data accuracy and consistency in the database. |
| Cardinality | Defines how many instances of one entity can relate to another entity. |

